    <description>Sub-title:&amp;quot;the Mother of Poltava&amp;quot; in The Wargamer Magazine #30 and is a supplement to the &amp;quot;Peter the Great&amp;quot; game in Wargamer #27 although this is a complete &amp;amp; separate game in itself requiring SOME of the components from the previous game, namely the RULES section.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The components for Lesnaja are: a small 8-1/2&amp;quot; by 11&amp;quot;, 6-Color Mapsheet; 60-cardboard counters- (die-cut); a RULES sheet; and players must provide their OWN [6]-sided DIE prior to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Mapsheet has a very Light YELLOW color overall with Light BLUE (Swamps), Dark BLUE (River), Light GREEN (Groves), Dark GREEN (Woods), RED (Objective &amp;amp; Supply Hexes), &amp;amp; BLACK (Roads, Town, Bridge, Ford, Set-up Letter Hexes). The Game counters are BLUE (Swedish) &amp;amp; GREEN (Russian) with BLACK print on both Front &amp;amp; Back. The RULES sheet is just over a page in length with a Historical commentary, with NEW Terrain, Optional Rules, Victory Conditions, and any Special Rules to be used pertaining to this particular battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
